A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Department of Education – Driver Education and Career and Technical
3 Education – Funding
4 (Driver Education and Career Education Act of 2025)
5 FOR the purpose of requiring, for certain fiscal years, the Governor to include in the annual
6 budget bill certain appropriations to the State Department of Education for the
7 Coalition for Public Safety Training in Schools, Inc., in Prince George’s County for
8 certain purposes related to driver education and career and technical education;
9 requiring the Department to hire an independent contractor to conduct a certain
10 annual evaluation; and generally relating to driver education and career and
11 technical education in the State.
12 BY adding to
13 Article – Education
14 Section 5–244
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
17 Preamble
18 WHEREAS, Career and technical education supports the efforts of the State to
19 provide students with skills and instruction set to international standards that will enable
20 the students to be successful in the 21st–century economy and productive citizens of the
21 State; and
22 WHEREAS, Career and technical education also provides high school students with
23 access to educational experiences and opportunities that enable the students to reach their
24 full promise and potential and to be ready for success in college and a rewarding career;
25 now, therefore,
