4 SENATE BILL 161
1 (C) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL HIRE AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR
2 THAT HAS EXPERIENCE EVALUATING EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS TO CONDUCT THE
3 ANNUAL EVALUATION REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(5) OF THIS SECTION.
4 (2) THE ANNUAL EVALUATION SHALL:
5 (I) BE CONDUCTED IN CONSULTATION WITH THE COALITION
6 FOR PUBLIC SAFETY TRAINING IN SCHOOLS, INC.; AND
7 (II) EXAMINE WHETHER FUNDING HAS:
8 1. INCREASED SUPPORT FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF
9 CAREER–READY STUDENTS;
10 2. PROVIDED PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT TO MORE
11 TEACHERS; AND
12 3. INCREASED THE OCCUPATIONAL LITERACY OF
13 STUDENTS.
14 (3) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1 EACH YEAR, BEGINNING IN 2028, THE
15 DEPARTMENT SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT ON THE ANNUAL EVALUATION REQUIRED
16 UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(5) OF THIS SECTION TO THE GOVERNOR AND THE STATE
17 SUPERINTENDENT AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE
18 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE, THE SPEAKER OF THE
19 HOUSE, THE SENATE COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, ENERGY, AND THE
20 ENVIRONMENT, AND THE HOUSE WAYS AND MEANS COMMITTEE.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
22 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 8 years and 1 month and, at the end of July
23 31, 2033, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
24 abrogated and of no further force and effect.

